WEBVTT

00:02.436 --> 00:03.502
[ Remote clicks ]

00:03.504 --> 00:05.037
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:07.574 --> 00:10.442
♪ I don't care what you say! ♪

00:11.778 --> 00:13.779
♪ I'm gonna do what I want
all day! ♪

00:13.781 --> 00:16.415
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:16.417 --> 00:18.350
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:18.352 --> 00:22.755
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:24.809 --> 00:27.144
♪♪

00:29.280 --> 00:32.715
Mm-hmm.
Let's see what we got here.

00:32.717 --> 00:34.951
Oh! Yes!

00:34.953 --> 00:37.019
Eh. I should've bought
the 500-piece.

00:37.021 --> 00:38.354
Mom.
- Hmm?

00:38.356 --> 00:40.957
Um, have you seen
my scissors anywhere?

00:40.959 --> 00:43.993
Try the, uh,
fridge or cupboard.

00:43.995 --> 00:45.795
[ Grunts ]

00:45.797 --> 00:47.663
Not over here.

00:47.665 --> 00:49.064
Oh, that's right.

00:49.066 --> 00:51.334
[ Chuckles ]
My hiding spot.

00:51.336 --> 00:53.469
Why the heck
did I buy this thing?

00:53.471 --> 00:55.638
Oh, oh, oh!

00:55.640 --> 00:57.707
Yes!

00:57.709 --> 00:59.042
All right, that's it.

00:59.044 --> 01:00.843
[ Clarence grunting ]

01:00.845 --> 01:02.679
Whatcha doing there,
booger?

01:02.681 --> 01:04.514
Just get this here.

01:04.516 --> 01:05.648
[ Chuckles ] There.

01:05.650 --> 01:07.917
I cut my hat.

01:07.919 --> 01:09.486
[ Chuckling ] Okay.
That needs a trim.

01:09.488 --> 01:10.987
You got a real mop-top
happening.

01:10.989 --> 01:12.488
How come I never
noticed that before?

01:12.490 --> 01:14.023
What? No, um...

01:14.025 --> 01:15.691
I need to go
to the bathroom.

01:15.693 --> 01:16.759
So...bye.
- Hey.

01:16.761 --> 01:17.894
See you later.
Wait! Clarence!

01:17.896 --> 01:19.195
[ Panting ]
No, no, no!

01:19.197 --> 01:20.363
[ Doorbell rings ]
Huh?

01:21.199 --> 01:23.032
Oh, hi, JT.
You made it.

01:23.034 --> 01:24.667
Oh, hey, Ms. Wendle.
You too.

01:24.669 --> 01:25.869
Um, so, uh...

01:25.871 --> 01:27.537
just the front yard, right?
That's right.

01:27.539 --> 01:28.939
And, you know,
if it gets too warm,

01:28.941 --> 01:30.873
I got a-a puzzle
going on in here

01:30.875 --> 01:32.876
and some cold beverages.

01:32.878 --> 01:34.377
Word.

01:36.548 --> 01:38.047
[ Grunts ]

01:38.049 --> 01:41.551
[ Lawnmower running ]

01:41.553 --> 01:42.886
Clarence: Mom.

01:42.888 --> 01:44.387
Someone's being
really nice

01:44.389 --> 01:46.889
and just mowing our lawn
for us.

01:46.891 --> 01:48.425
Yeah, that's JT.

01:49.428 --> 01:50.760
Wow.

01:50.762 --> 01:52.095
[ Upbeat rock music plays ]

01:52.097 --> 01:53.229
♪ Yeah! ♪

01:53.231 --> 01:55.765
♪ You don't get me ♪

01:55.767 --> 01:57.099
♪ Oh! ♪

01:57.101 --> 01:58.901
Um, hello.
♪ You won't forget me ♪

01:58.903 --> 02:00.570
Excuse me! Excuse me!

02:00.572 --> 02:02.205
♪ Just like a fighter in... ♪

02:02.207 --> 02:03.572
Hello? Dingdong!

02:03.574 --> 02:04.741
Aah!

02:06.945 --> 02:08.911
[ Lawnmower stops ]
'Sup?

02:08.913 --> 02:10.914
I really like your hair.

02:10.916 --> 02:12.048
Thanks, little man.

02:12.050 --> 02:13.049
You're welcome.

02:13.051 --> 02:14.751
I'm Clarence.

02:14.753 --> 02:15.952
John Thomas.

02:15.954 --> 02:17.920
Um, what are you
listening to?

02:17.922 --> 02:19.122
Iron Tiger.

02:19.124 --> 02:20.590
Oh. [ Chuckles ] Cool.

02:20.592 --> 02:21.924
Wait up. Wha-- Uh --
Hol-- Wait up?

02:21.926 --> 02:23.259
You heard of Iron Tiger?

02:23.261 --> 02:26.095
Well...sort of.

02:26.097 --> 02:28.131
Oh, man! You need these
way more than me.

02:28.133 --> 02:29.499
Um...sure.

02:29.501 --> 02:31.801
♪ I'm comin' to getcha, getcha ♪

02:31.803 --> 02:33.236
Hmm.

02:33.238 --> 02:35.305
♪ Just like a lone wolf
on the prowl ♪

02:35.307 --> 02:37.440
♪ You will hear me howl ♪

02:37.442 --> 02:39.108
♪ Owww! ♪

02:39.110 --> 02:41.110
♪ I'm comin' to getcha ♪

02:41.112 --> 02:43.112
[ Vocalizing ]
♪ Yeah! ♪

02:43.114 --> 02:44.147
♪ You don't get me ♪

02:44.149 --> 02:45.314
So, what do you think?

02:45.316 --> 02:46.650
[ Chuckles ]
- Sounded pretty good to me.

02:46.652 --> 02:47.684
"Pretty good"?

02:47.686 --> 02:49.018
You know,
Stephanie was all like,

02:49.020 --> 02:51.120
"Oh, is Iron Tiger good?"

02:51.122 --> 02:53.122
I'm like, "[Scoffs] No duh.

02:53.124 --> 02:55.858
Of course it's good.
It's the best."

02:55.860 --> 02:57.626
Also, I like
that one guy

02:57.628 --> 02:59.796
who makes all
the monkey sounds like...

02:59.798 --> 03:01.264
[ Chattering ]

03:01.266 --> 03:02.632
Oh, Keith Mack?

03:02.634 --> 03:03.666
[ Guitar riff plays ]

03:03.668 --> 03:05.635
He's the reason
I got my rattail.

03:05.637 --> 03:07.603
It opens
all kinds of doors.

03:07.605 --> 03:08.971
Like car doors?

03:08.973 --> 03:10.640
<i>All</i> kinds.
- Wow.

03:10.642 --> 03:13.977
And if anybody messes with it,
they get<i> this.</i>

03:13.979 --> 03:15.645
Hyah!

03:15.647 --> 03:16.846
Aah! Huh?

03:16.848 --> 03:17.880
Oh.

03:17.882 --> 03:19.482
[ Laughs ]

03:19.484 --> 03:21.551
[ Chuckles ] You really get it,
don't you, little man?

03:21.553 --> 03:23.720
Um, I guess so.

03:23.722 --> 03:27.023
Hey, would you want
to come over to my house?

03:29.160 --> 03:30.660
Mom! Mom!

03:30.662 --> 03:33.696
This is JT, and he's, like,
the coolest person ever.

03:33.698 --> 03:36.399
And can you
cut my hair like his?

03:36.401 --> 03:38.801
Hmm. All right.
But only for a week.

03:38.803 --> 03:40.036
[ Scissors clicking ]

03:40.038 --> 03:42.171
Check that tail,
little man.

03:42.173 --> 03:43.973
Oh, my gosh!

03:43.975 --> 03:45.307
It looks just like yours!

03:45.309 --> 03:47.410
Hey, do you want to see
how to draw muscles?

03:47.412 --> 03:49.044
Whoa.
[ Chuckles ]

03:49.046 --> 03:51.080
Little shading right here.

03:51.082 --> 03:52.515
[ Grunts, sighs ]

03:52.517 --> 03:54.517
Here's a little feast
for your eyes.

03:54.519 --> 03:55.518
Whoa!

03:55.520 --> 03:57.987
He's got like
a jillion, gillion abs!

03:57.989 --> 04:00.657
So, what else
is fun to do?

04:00.659 --> 04:01.857
Mm...

04:01.859 --> 04:02.891
I know.

04:02.893 --> 04:04.394
Mm-hmm.

04:04.396 --> 04:05.862
Where you going, hon?

04:05.864 --> 04:07.230
Going out.
- All right.

04:07.232 --> 04:09.565
Uh, uh, JT,
- can you keep an eye on him?

04:09.567 --> 04:10.834
Word.

04:10.836 --> 04:12.201
[ Rock music plays ]

04:12.203 --> 04:14.604
Vroom, vroom,
vroom, vroom, vroom!

04:14.606 --> 04:15.938
Need a ride?

04:15.940 --> 04:19.041
♪ Out on the track,
hair out the back ♪

04:19.043 --> 04:20.710
Bye, Gunner! Love you!

04:20.712 --> 04:23.412
♪ Thin as a string
or the tail of a rat ♪

04:23.414 --> 04:26.248
♪ I don't care
what other people think ♪

04:26.250 --> 04:28.284
♪ I got a 'do that's cooler
than a new ice rink ♪ Huh?

04:28.286 --> 04:30.219
Man: - Bring me a number 44.
Yeah.

04:30.221 --> 04:33.189
♪ Livin' tailer than life ♪

04:33.191 --> 04:35.591
Hey, y'all
staying clear of school?

04:35.593 --> 04:37.226
[ Scoffs ]
What do you think?

04:37.228 --> 04:38.394
It's JT.

04:38.396 --> 04:41.230
Um, I have never been
in a school.

04:41.232 --> 04:42.799
Yeah, that's what
I'm talking about.

04:42.801 --> 04:45.034
[ Gulps ]

04:45.036 --> 04:46.369
[ Music continues ]

04:46.371 --> 04:47.570
Here, watch this.

04:47.572 --> 04:49.205
Hmm?

04:49.207 --> 04:51.074
How much for this one?

04:51.076 --> 04:53.242
[ Grunts ]

04:53.244 --> 04:55.578
Hmm. Hmm?

04:57.148 --> 04:58.814
It's on the house.

04:58.816 --> 05:00.083
[ Gasps ] All right!

05:00.085 --> 05:00.950
[ Laughs ]

05:00.952 --> 05:02.252
You see, little man?

05:02.254 --> 05:04.620
This is the way
of the rattail.

05:04.622 --> 05:07.490
Us tailers, we got to look out
for each other.

05:07.492 --> 05:10.393
These other ants of society,
they just don't get it.

05:10.395 --> 05:11.927
Oh, hi, there.

05:11.929 --> 05:14.430
They're just marching down
the anthill of conformity.

05:14.432 --> 05:15.665
They make me sick.

05:15.667 --> 05:19.235
Yeah! Go back to your anthill,
you sick man.

05:19.237 --> 05:21.437
Excuse me?
I...didn't catch you.

05:21.439 --> 05:23.172
You've adapted well.

05:23.174 --> 05:25.341
I knew
you wasn't an ant.

05:25.343 --> 05:27.911
Take 'er easy,
Clarence.

05:30.449 --> 05:33.449
[ Indistinct conversations,
school bell rings ]

05:33.451 --> 05:36.185
[ Upbeat rock music plays ]

05:36.187 --> 05:37.854
Ow.

05:38.956 --> 05:40.990
Huh?

05:40.992 --> 05:43.626
Clarence: Hey, Jeff.

05:43.628 --> 05:45.995
Hi, Clar--
Wh-Wh-What is that?

05:45.997 --> 05:47.162
Eh, it's just my tail.

05:47.164 --> 05:48.163
Pretty cool, huh?

05:48.165 --> 05:50.132
No!
It's unsanitary.

05:50.134 --> 05:54.504
Okay! We are going to be
learning about insects today.

05:54.506 --> 05:57.339
Oh. Uh...
- interesting hair, Clarence.

05:57.341 --> 05:58.975
[ Chuckles ]
Are you jealous?

05:58.977 --> 06:00.309
[ Chuckles ]

06:00.311 --> 06:02.512
Got to show the man my plan,
am I right?

06:02.514 --> 06:04.613
What?

06:04.615 --> 06:08.283
So, an insect's skeleton is actually on the
outside. Psst! Brady. Did you see my hair?

06:08.285 --> 06:09.885
Yoo-hoo!
Brady, check it out.

06:09.887 --> 06:12.187
If this part was the thorax,
- Brady.

06:12.189 --> 06:13.689
okay, then what do we call this part
-- You don't want to miss out on this.

06:13.691 --> 06:15.057
Earth to Brady.
Look at this.

06:15.059 --> 06:16.459
Uh, Clarence.

06:16.461 --> 06:19.695
Melany, aren't we all
just society's ants?

06:19.697 --> 06:21.030
Interesting point,
Clarence,

06:21.032 --> 06:22.564
but not exactly
what I was looking for.

06:22.566 --> 06:24.333
Yep.
- Um...okay, forget that.

06:24.335 --> 06:27.036
Mm. Got to let
the tail breathe.

06:27.038 --> 06:28.838
[ Groaning ]

06:28.840 --> 06:31.307
Aah! Ms. Baker,
may I please switch seats?

06:31.309 --> 06:33.409
Y-Yeah, o-okay, Jeff.

06:33.411 --> 06:35.178
Uh, why don't you switch
with Crendle?

06:35.180 --> 06:36.512
It's okay, Jeff.

06:36.514 --> 06:39.716
Not everybody can handle
the life of a tailer.

06:39.718 --> 06:42.418
But<i> you</i> know what's up,
don't you, Crendle?

06:42.420 --> 06:44.420
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

06:47.926 --> 06:49.992
Doing -- - Aw! Gross!
Looking pretty cool, huh?

06:49.994 --> 06:51.928
Ew!

06:56.701 --> 07:00.336
Kickball!
Hey, everyone! Kickball!

07:00.338 --> 07:02.004
[ Indistinct talking ]

07:02.006 --> 07:03.373
Tailers love kickball.

07:03.375 --> 07:05.208
Okay, so,
- I'm going to pick first.

07:05.210 --> 07:07.843
Psst! Yo. Hey. Jeff.

07:07.845 --> 07:10.045
Hey, Jeff.
Number-one tail boy right here.

07:10.047 --> 07:11.380
Breehn.

07:11.382 --> 07:14.050
[ Scoffs ] Breehn.
That's a rookie move.

07:14.052 --> 07:15.952
And I'll take Dustin.

07:15.954 --> 07:18.220
Mavis.
- Oh. Mm.

07:18.222 --> 07:20.590
Okay.
Nathan: Uh, Guyler.

07:20.592 --> 07:22.558
What?
- Percy.

07:22.560 --> 07:24.727
Um, hello?
Standing right here.

07:24.729 --> 07:26.262
Mm. Camden.

07:26.264 --> 07:27.297
Oh.

07:27.299 --> 07:29.598
Uh, all right.

07:29.600 --> 07:32.468
Yeah!
Jeff, I'm on your team!

07:32.470 --> 07:35.070
Sorry, Clarence.
You can't be on my team.

07:35.072 --> 07:36.940
[ Wistful music plays ]
[ Scoffs ] Whatever.

07:36.942 --> 07:38.708
Clarence,
you're my best friend,

07:38.710 --> 07:40.576
but that thing growing
from the back of your head,

07:40.578 --> 07:42.878
well, it's changing you,
and I don't like it.

07:42.880 --> 07:44.914
Even if you<i> were</i>
acting normally --

07:44.916 --> 07:46.082
which you aren't --

07:46.084 --> 07:48.284
I'd still be concerned
with my team's image.

07:48.286 --> 07:50.653
I'm sorry,
but not today.

07:55.259 --> 07:57.961
[ Indistinct talking ]

08:00.998 --> 08:02.265
Ow! Hmm.

08:02.267 --> 08:03.666
[ Groans ]

08:03.668 --> 08:05.801
Well, it's been fun,
little guy,

08:05.803 --> 08:09.639
but I just don't think
I'm cut out to be a tailer.

08:12.576 --> 08:14.076
Nathan: Heads-up!

08:14.078 --> 08:15.111
[ Gasps ]

08:15.113 --> 08:16.145
Uh, s-sorry.

08:16.147 --> 08:17.413
Clarence?

08:17.415 --> 08:19.114
Don't worry.
- I-I'm just getting your ball.

08:19.116 --> 08:20.749
No, no, it's fine.

08:20.751 --> 08:22.952
[ Chuckles ]
- Glad you came to your senses.

08:22.954 --> 08:25.287
Breehn won't stop
- complaining about his feet.

08:25.289 --> 08:26.789
Why don't you come
take his place?

08:26.791 --> 08:28.624
Oh. Okay.

08:28.626 --> 08:30.126
Hmm.

08:30.128 --> 08:31.327
Mm.

08:31.329 --> 08:33.095
Breehn, tag team.
Tagging you out.

08:33.097 --> 08:38.968
[ Upbeat rock music plays ]
[ Vocalizing ]

08:38.970 --> 08:40.536
I'm sorry, JT.

08:40.538 --> 08:43.205
We had a nice run,
you and me, but this --

08:43.207 --> 08:44.974
this is
for your own good.

08:46.144 --> 08:47.376
[ Gasps ] Wha--

08:47.378 --> 08:48.677
W-Wait!

08:48.679 --> 08:49.979
Goodbye!
- My tail!

08:49.981 --> 08:51.647
You're welcome.
- Come back to me!

08:51.649 --> 08:53.215
No, no, no,
no, no, no!

08:53.217 --> 08:54.483
You bozo!

08:54.485 --> 08:55.985
I brought you into
the rattail life,

08:55.987 --> 08:58.153
and this is how
you repay me?!

08:58.155 --> 08:59.355
Hy--
- Aah!

08:59.357 --> 09:01.491
[ Groans ]

09:01.493 --> 09:04.894
I just, you know...

09:04.896 --> 09:06.195
[ Sighs ]

09:06.197 --> 09:07.830
Everyone else,

09:07.832 --> 09:11.500
they're just chitchatting
all the time face-to-face,

09:11.502 --> 09:12.868
with words,

09:12.870 --> 09:16.238
but I need --
I need this stuff.

09:16.240 --> 09:18.507
I-It just helps,
you know?

09:18.509 --> 09:20.043
[ Sighs ]

09:20.045 --> 09:23.813
Yeah, but my friend Jeff says
that what matters

09:23.815 --> 09:25.681
is you should just be me.

09:25.683 --> 09:29.018
Maybe, but you're more of
a baller, shot-caller than me.

09:29.020 --> 09:30.419
I need my tail.

09:30.421 --> 09:34.023
Well...
maybe this will help.

09:34.025 --> 09:35.558
[ Guitar riff plays ]

09:35.560 --> 09:37.359
[ Grunts ]

09:37.361 --> 09:38.928
What do you think?

09:38.930 --> 09:41.330
[ Sighs ]
It looks awesome.

09:41.332 --> 09:42.565
Why don't people like it?

09:42.567 --> 09:44.033
Listen, little man.

09:44.035 --> 09:47.570
You can't expect anyone
to just get the rattail life.

09:47.572 --> 09:49.505
You have to feel it
in<i> here --</i>

09:49.507 --> 09:52.541
and more importantly,
<i>here.</i>

09:52.543 --> 09:54.443
Yeah! Yeah!

09:54.445 --> 09:57.046
So, how old are you now?

09:57.048 --> 09:59.548
You got yourself
a little boyfriend, eh?

09:59.550 --> 10:02.517
I bet you're breaking
a bunch of hearts, huh?

10:02.519 --> 10:04.053
They're all lining
up to --

10:04.055 --> 10:05.521
What do they do,
hold hands now?

10:05.523 --> 10:07.389
It's probably --
Or you know what?

10:07.391 --> 10:09.458
So, guys, Clarence said

10:09.460 --> 10:11.860
that he made something
for the class today!

10:11.862 --> 10:13.796
Um, I made one of these
for everyone,

10:13.798 --> 10:15.465
so just go ahead
and pass them out.

10:15.467 --> 10:16.899
[ All groan ]

10:16.901 --> 10:20.403
Guh! Uh, Clarence, is that a --
is that a box of hair?

10:20.405 --> 10:21.604
Yeah.

10:21.606 --> 10:23.606
I made rattails
for everyone --

10:23.608 --> 10:25.240
even one for you,
Ms. Baker.

10:25.242 --> 10:26.909
Here you go.
- [ Shakily ] Oho!

10:26.911 --> 10:27.910
Thank you.

10:27.912 --> 10:29.544
Clarence!
No one likes rattails!

10:29.546 --> 10:30.746
Nuh-unh.

10:30.748 --> 10:32.748
This way,
everyone can try one,

10:32.750 --> 10:35.584
and if they don't like it,
you can just take it off.

10:35.586 --> 10:37.219
It could be fun.

10:37.221 --> 10:40.055
Uh, well, yeah, I guess
it's a little, uh, cool.

10:40.057 --> 10:41.757
Uh, but, seriously,
Clarence, you can't --

10:41.759 --> 10:42.791
Nathan: How does it look?
- What?

10:42.793 --> 10:44.093
How does it look?

10:44.095 --> 10:46.262
[ Laughter ]

10:46.264 --> 10:49.431
[ Indistinct talking ]

10:49.433 --> 10:50.733
No, no, no!

10:50.735 --> 10:51.934
It's fine. It's fine.
Stop touching me!

10:51.936 --> 10:53.269
It's got to...
Oh, it's tickling me.

10:53.271 --> 10:54.437
There we go.

10:54.439 --> 10:55.771
Ohhh.

10:55.773 --> 10:57.673
I actually
look pretty good.

10:57.675 --> 10:59.475
[ Chuckles ] Word.

11:03.279 --> 11:05.415
♪ Early to bed ♪

11:06.650 --> 11:08.918
♪ Early to rise ♪

11:10.321 --> 11:13.790
♪ Picking my nose ♪
